## When working in this repo

1. Read `AGENTS.md` (this file) first. Then read your CLI overlay
   (`CLAUDE.md` / `CODEX.md` / `PI.md`).
2. Read `wiki/SCHEMA.md` before any wiki write.
3. Apply rules matched to the file extension (`.agent-os/rules/<lang>.md`).
4. Treat `wiki/` as authoritative — read before re-deriving.
5. Every non-obvious decision becomes an ADR in `wiki/plan/adr/` or
   `wiki/plan/packages/<pkg>/adr/`.
6. Every non-obvious learning becomes a wiki page.
7. Append project decisions to `.agent-os/memories.md` (private personal
   memories go to `~/.agent-os/memories.md`).
8. Never commit `.env*`, credentials, or anything in `.gitignore`.
9. Never `git push --force` and never use `--no-verify` without explicit
   user permission.
10. Use conventional commits: imperative subject ≤ 50 chars, optional body.

