## The wiki — Karpathy LLM-Wiki pattern

The wiki is the agent's long-term memory. Mental model: instead of re-deriving
knowledge from raw sources on every query, the agent maintains a persistent,
compounding markdown knowledge base.

| Folder | What lives here | Mutability |
|---|---|---|
| `wiki/raw/` | Immutable sources (PDFs, transcripts, screenshots) | never modify |
| `wiki/sources/` | One card per ingested source | agent writes |
| `wiki/entities/` | Orgs / products / people / tools | agent writes |
| `wiki/concepts/` | Ideas / patterns / techniques | agent writes |
| `wiki/questions/` | Resolved Q&A | agent writes |
| `wiki/IDEAS-details/` | Per-ID detail blocks | agent writes |
| `wiki/plan/` | Cross-cutting planning docs + ADRs + packages docs | agent writes |
| `wiki/log.md` | Append-only audit log | agent appends |

Required frontmatter on every wiki page:

```yaml
---
title: <human title>
type: source | entity | concept | question | adr | package | plan
tags: [kebab-case, list]
updated: YYYY-MM-DD
sources: [optional wikilinks to source pages]
---
```

Wikilinks: `[[category/slug]]` or `[[category/slug|display text]]`. Without
`.md` suffix. Link liberally — a link to a missing page is a TODO marker, not
an error. Contradictions surface explicitly:

```markdown
> Contradicts [[other-page]] as of YYYY-MM-DD — <one-sentence reason>
```

Operations: ingest, query, lint. See `.agent-os/skills/llm-wiki/SKILL.md` if
installed, or the canonical workflow in `wiki/SCHEMA.md`.

## Conventions

- **Commits**: Conventional Commits. `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `chore:`,
  `refactor:`, `test:`. Subject imperative, ≤ 50 chars.
- **Push policy**: never auto-push. The user pushes.
- **Hooks**: hooks are mandatory; `--no-verify` is forbidden.
- **Confidentiality**: treat private repo content as private. Never paste
  source files into external services.
- **PM tool**: see `.agent-os/rules/{{PM_TOOL}}.md` for issue body format,
  state transitions, label taxonomy.

## Autonomy mode

`.agent-os/settings.json` declares `autonomy_mode` ∈ {M0, M1, M2, M3}:

- **M0** — read-only / dry-run. No file writes.
- **M1** — write files; never run shell commands.
- **M2** — write + run sandboxed shell.
- **M3** — write + run shell + auto-commit. (No auto-push at any tier.)

Default: M2. Bump explicitly when you trust the task.

